igh&#039;">s</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a title="IPA for English" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" rel="nofollow"><span title="/i/ &#039;y&#039; in &#039;happy&#039;">i</span></a></span><span class="IPA" title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)"><a title="IPA for English" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" rel="nofollow">/</a></span></span> is the <a class="mw-redirect" title="Capital (political)" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capital_%28political%29" rel="nofollow">capital</a> of the <a title="U.S. state" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._state" rel="nofollow">U.S. state</a> of <a title="Florida" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida" rel="nofollow">Florida</a>. It is the <a title="County seat" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/County_seat" rel="nofollow">county seat</a> and only incorporated municipality in <a title="Leon County, Florida" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leon_County,_Florida" rel="nofollow">Leon County</a>, and is the 128th largest city in the <a title="United States" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States" rel="nofollow">United States</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tallahassee,_Florida#cite_note-4" rel="nofollow"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> Tallahassee became the capital of Florida, then the <a title="Florida Territory" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida_Territory" rel="nofollow">Florida Territory</a>, in 1824. In 2010, the population recorded by the <a class="mw-redirect" title="U.S. Census Bureau" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._Census_Bureau" rel="nofollow">U.S. Census Bureau</a> was 181,376,<sup id="cite_ref-PopEstBigCities_5-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tallahassee,_Florida#cite_note-PopEstBigCities-5" rel="nofollow"><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup> and the <a class="mw-redirect" title="Tallahassee, Florida Metropolitan Statistical Area" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tallahassee,_Florida_Metropolitan_Statistical_Area" rel="nofollow">Tallahassee metropolitan area</a> is 375,371 as of 2012.<sup id="cite_ref-UrbanTallahassee_6-0" class="reference"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tallahassee,_Florida#cite_note-UrbanTallahassee-6" rel="nofollow"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
